==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Carpetbagger
<hw>Car"pet*bag`ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An adventurer;
-- a term of contempt for a Northern man seeking private gain or
political advancement in the southern part of the United States after
the Civil War (1865)<-- used now for any politician moving to a new
location to take advantage of more favorable chances for
election-->.</def> <mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>carpeted</ent>⟦br⟧
